1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,752
We have a first-period class tomorrow.

2
00:00:02,752 --> 00:00:04,254
Wash up and go to sleep.

3
00:00:04,254 --> 00:00:05,213
Don't be late tomorrow.

4
00:00:06,548 --> 00:00:09,801
You're such a nag.

5
00:00:09,801 --> 00:00:11,553
Thanks for today.

6
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:14,264
Get home safe.

7
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:26,192
I think I know how you feel...

8
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,236
and I know you'll reject me...

9
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:35,702
but what am I supposed to do when I can't give up?

10
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:38,121
Why did it have to be you?

11
00:00:55,472 --> 00:01:01,269
I shouldn't be the one wavering.

12
00:01:01,269 --> 00:01:07,859
I truly don't want to lose you,

13
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:13,865
and I want you by my side forever,

14
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:21,998
but our relationship shouldn't change.

15
00:01:21,998 --> 00:01:27,378
It's right for me to keep pretending I don't know, right?

16
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:33,885
If you knew I felt this way about you,

17
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:40,016
how would you react?

18
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:48,650
The weather is nice.

19
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,110
I know, right?

20
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,867
Hey, Kim Siwoo!

21
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,160
What took you so long?

22
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,329
What are you doing in the middle of the day?

23
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:02,831
We have a major class next.

24
00:02:02,831 --> 00:02:06,334
It's a waste to sit in a lecture on a beautiful day like this.

25
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:07,836
Siwoo.

26
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:09,212
Cover my attendance for me.

27
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:11,297
Covering for you is fine once or twice, but...

28
00:02:11,297 --> 00:02:12,173
Give it a rest.

29
00:02:12,298 --> 00:02:14,676
Oh, come on. Siwoo, take a seat.

30
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,596
Lee Seongjae, you're doing it again.

31
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:22,016
That's why people keep misunderstanding.

32
00:02:22,016 --> 00:02:23,935
Is Kim Siwoo yours or something?

33
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:27,105
Yeah, he's mine.

34
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:29,858
And this...

35
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:30,650
is yours.

36
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,701
Just finish that and get up.

37
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:41,202
I'm not covering your attendance today.

38
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:42,829
Why?

39
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:43,997
Just this once.

40
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,415
You've said that a hundred times.

41
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:47,083
Seriously, just this once.

42
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:48,877
No.

43
00:02:49,043 --> 00:02:50,253
Just for today.

44
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,005
I said no.

45
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:57,552
Where are you going?

46
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,429
Restroom.

47
00:02:59,429 --> 00:03:00,138
Why?

48
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:01,431
Wanna come with me?

49
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:02,682
Just hurry up and go.

50
00:03:03,808 --> 00:03:05,059
I'll be right back.

51
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,232
Let's start packing up.

52
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,275
So we can leave when Seongjae gets back.

53
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:13,860
How long are you going to keep this up?

54
00:03:14,819 --> 00:03:15,737
Keep what up?

55
00:03:16,112 --> 00:03:18,031
How long are you going to clean up after Lee Seongjae?

56
00:03:20,283 --> 00:03:22,327
You hate drinking,

57
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:25,371
and you hate loud places even more.

58
00:03:25,371 --> 00:03:28,208
But you practically live at bars just to follow him around.

59
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,042
Does that make any sense?

60
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:30,543
What are you trying to say?

61
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:32,754
It's just frustrating to watch.

62
00:03:32,754 --> 00:03:34,631
I've been watching you two for two years.

63
00:03:35,006 --> 00:03:37,467
Wouldn't it be weirder if I didn't notice?

64
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:41,596
You like Lee Seongjae.

65
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:46,601
I know you try not to make it obvious,

66
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:48,144
but how could it not be?

67
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,813
If you see me trying, just pretend you don't know.

68
00:03:50,813 --> 00:03:51,981
Hey, Kim Siwoo.

69
00:03:52,106 --> 00:03:54,192
Then what should I do?

70
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:55,568
Should I confess my feelings to Seongjae?

71
00:03:57,820 --> 00:04:00,240
To a jerk who draws a line at "friends" and won't let me cross it?

72
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,449
What am I...

73
00:04:01,866 --> 00:04:04,035
What the hell am I supposed to do?

74
00:04:04,035 --> 00:04:05,620
I'm sorry.

75
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,997
I crossed the line.

76
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,458
It's between you and Lee Seongjae.

77
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:16,172
I know you're just worried about me...

78
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:18,925
but I don't know what to do either.

79
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,388
I should control my expression.

80
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:24,222
Huh?

81
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:27,767
I'm going to leave first.

82
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:32,355
Tell Seongjae to go to class.

83
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:35,233
Siwoo!

84
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:39,612
Pack your things.

85
00:04:39,821 --> 00:04:41,406
Siwoo said you need to go to class.

86
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:41,906
Huh?

87
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:43,032
You're leaving?

88
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,327
Getting nagged by one person is enough.

89
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,955
I don't want Siwoo to hate me.

90
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:50,123
Hey.

91
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:50,957
Hey.

92
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,390
You were here?

93
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:11,144
Is something wrong?

94
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,521
You haven't said a word since the lecture earlier.

95
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:16,024
Isn't it weirder to talk during a lecture?

96
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:21,487
Why are you being so edgy today?

97
00:05:21,487 --> 00:05:23,781
Is it because I asked you to cover my attendance earlier?

98
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:25,950
Or is it because of the drinking?

99
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:31,372
It's not like it's only happened once or twice.

100
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,752
Seriously, what's wrong with you?

101
00:05:35,752 --> 00:05:37,754
You have to use your words.

102
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:44,093
Did Cha Dojin say some weird stuff earlier?

103
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:45,636
He was doing it earlier, too.

104
00:05:45,636 --> 00:05:48,014
Saying that the juniors think we're dating or something.

105
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:51,184
So I set him straight.

106
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:53,561
He won't spout nonsense anymore.

107
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:55,104
Why would we be dating?

108
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:57,940
We're just friends.

109
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:03,946
Siwoo.

110
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:07,450
If you ask me,

111
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:10,286
you're just too overprotective of me.

112
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:12,789
Honestly, it must be annoying for you sometimes.

113
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,457
You hate loud places,

114
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:15,666
and you don't even drink.

115
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,460
You only come because of me.

116
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,380
You sure know it well.

117
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:23,466
Of course I do.

118
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:26,427
I've always felt bad about it.

119
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:29,555
If you don't want to, you don't have to come.

120
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:33,309
You told me to stay by your side and just drink soda.

121
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,937
Hey, I was just saying that.

122
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:38,689
Why would I force someone who doesn't want to?

123
00:06:39,315 --> 00:06:42,610
It's not like we can stick together forever.

124
00:06:42,610 --> 00:06:44,153
We'll have to date and stuff...

125
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,782
Did I say I hated it?

126
00:06:48,991 --> 00:06:49,700
Huh?

127
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:53,162
When did I ever say I hated it?

128
00:06:53,162 --> 00:06:55,665
Do you really think I'm forcing myself to be by your side?

129
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:57,500
No...

130
00:06:58,167 --> 00:07:01,212
It's just that people keep misunderstanding us...

131
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:05,049
Honestly, it's a bit uncomfortable for me to be misunderstood like that, too.

132
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:06,843
Uncomfortable?

133
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:09,720
You feel the same way.

134
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,806
You don't have to take care of me.

135
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:14,142
You don't have to come to drinking parties.

136
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:17,228
You don't need to stay by my side if it means dealing with those misunderstandings.

137
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:20,606
I have never, not even once, forced myself to accommodate you.

138
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:23,818
I did it because I liked it.

139
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:25,445
I just liked being with you,

140
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,488
so I endured those boring times.

141
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:29,240
Siwoo, that's not what I meant.

142
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:32,493
But I guess you hate people misunderstanding us more.

143
00:07:33,202 --> 00:07:37,081
So much that my kindness has become burdensome and uncomfortable.

144
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:39,000
I was just thinking of you...

145
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,918
More like you were thinking of yourself.

146
00:07:40,918 --> 00:07:43,129
You're the one who hates being misunderstood.

147
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:48,468
I guess the very act of me being with you

148
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,762
is something that causes misunderstandings.

149
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,808
Hey, Kim Siwoo.

150
00:07:56,809 --> 00:07:59,479
Just like you wanted,

151
00:07:59,479 --> 00:08:01,397
I'll stop caring about your business from now on.

152
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:02,815
Happy now?

153
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:09,030
I shouldn't have worried in the first place.

154
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:10,865
Why did I even hide it?

155
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:12,116
What?

156
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,620
Forget it.

157
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:20,875
I could never remain just your friend for the rest of my life anyway.

158
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:25,296
Hey, Kim Siwoo!

159
00:08:27,715 --> 00:08:32,011
What is there to like about a coward like me?

160
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:36,516
Why do you like me when I don't even have the courage to accept your confession?

161
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,142
Making me feel so sorry...
